SIMPLE: flaunt
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flaunt
<hw>Flaunt</hw> <pr>(fl⟦aum⟧nt ⟦or⟧ fl⟦add⟧nt; 277)</pr>, <pos>v.
i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Flaunted</conjf>;
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>. <conjf>Flaunting</conjf>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[Cf. dial. G. <ets>flandern</ets> to flutter, wave; perh. akin to
E. <ets>flatter</ets>, <ets>flutter</ets>.]</ety> <def>To throw or
spread out; to flutter; to move ostentatiously; <as>as, a
<ex>flaunting</ex> show</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You <qex>flaunt</qex> about the streets in your new gilt
chariot.</q> <rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One <qex>flaunts</qex> in rags, one flutters in brocade.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flaunt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Flaunt
<hw>Flaunt</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To display ostentatiously; to
make an impudent show of.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧If you've got it,
<xex>flaunt</xex> it.⟦rdquo⟧⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flaunt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Flaunt
<hw>Flaunt</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Anything displayed for show.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In these my borrowed <qex>flaunts</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flauntingly</ent>⟦br⟧
